articles.author: Simon Patterson
articles.title: How Australian GP schedule swap can influence MotoGP title race - The Race
articles.description: With the Australian Grand Prix sprint at risk of being lost now the Phillip Island schedule has been revised, there's also a potentially significant impact on Pecco Bagnaia's and Jorge Martin's close MotoGP title fight
articles.content: The Australian Grand Prix's big schedule shake-up comes in an attempt to dodge impending high winds and bad weather - but, with the MotoGP sprint race at risk of being lost, there's also a potential … [+3970 chars]
